This is not my usual post, but I love new beginnings, and today’s Winter Solstice gives us just that. It’s the perfect day to focus on your aspirations for 2023. Anyone who truly knows me, knows that 369 are my numbers, and there is a reason for it.  Not only are they divine in their own right, but when paired together, they are absolutely magical. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
A fun way to manifest some of your nearest and dearest desires closest to your heart, is to use the 369 method. First, create an affirmation, and make sure it’s in the present tense. Start out small, but make it good! Then do the following. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
• Write down your affirmation three times as soon as you wake up in the morning.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
• Write down your affirmation six times during the afternoon.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
• Write your affirmation nine times before you go to bed.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Writing it down turns your thoughts into emotions, and thus into reality. So I’d love to hear some of your aspirations. Mine for today is “Everything that I do today is supporting my health & happiness.” And most importantly, you have to match your actions to your words, only way to co-create your new reality.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​

2️⃣ Albert Hadley, often hailed as 'the dean of American decorators,' was a pioneering force in the industry. His iconic modern style and ability to seamlessly blend various design influences continue to inspire designers today.

3️⃣ Barbara Barry, the revered matriarch of American interior design, has been a true icon since opening her first studio in 1985. Her elegant designs beautifully incorporate elements from nature, bringing a sense of tranquility and sophistication to every space.

4️⃣ Kelly Wearstler, also known as the queen of maximalism, has a bold and innovative approach that constantly pushes boundaries, making her an endless source of inspiration for all design enthusiasts (including myself). 💫

Maddox always knew best, and this wasn’t any different. It’s no coincidence that she came to me on Christmas Day, because it was on the same day 17 years ago that Maddox was adopted.
